xinput-plus (6.6.4-1) unstable; urgency=medium

  * New upstream release 6.6.4.
  * debian/control: bump Standards-Version to 4.7.3 (no changes required).
  * debian/control: add Suggests: qt6ct, qt6-style-kvantum.
  * debian/copyright: fix DEP-5 format — add Format: header, remove inline
    comments, fix stanza indentation, cover all source files.
  * debian/rules: install man page; translate comments to English; tighten
    lrelease glob guard to check for .ts files before invoking lrelease.
  * debian/watch: tighten version regex (\d+ instead of \d).
  * debian/xinput-plus.1: fix .TH macro (add date, version, section title);
    add OPTIONS and FILES sections; complete SYNOPSIS.
  * debian/xinput-plus.desktop: use human-readable Name; add Spanish
    localization entries; set Categories=Settings;HardwareSettings;
  * debian/xinput-plus.metainfo.xml: add missing releases; replace
    deprecated <developer_name> with <developer>; add bugtracker URL.
  * xinput-plus.py: rename confusing "Extended mode (CTM)" checkbox to
    "Extra speed (for slow devices)"; fix _qm_candidates logic bug; remove
    dead code and Spanish comments; fix grammatical error in About text.
  * i18n/xinput-plus_es.ts: update Spanish translations for renamed
    checkbox and updated About dialog text; remove obsolete entries.

